identifications.body: I'd agree with P. metricus. Useful traits are as follows: abdomen lacking red markings beyond segment 2 with the remainder black; dark mark around the ocelli separated from the dark mark around the antennal bases; dark marks on the top of the thorax (scutum) variable but normally with red dominating; when visible, the underside of the second abdominal segment from the body should be noticeably convex, almost squared off versus a smooth and gradual curvature.
